title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Generate a Wayang plan that computes, for each nation and each year, the total profit for all parts whose name contains the substring ‘green’. Profit is defined as (l_extendedprice * (1 - l_discount)) - (ps_supplycost * l_quantity). Join the part, supplier, lineitem, partsupp, orders, and nation tables through their keys. Extract the order year, filter parts so that p_name contains ‘green’, and group the results by nation and year. Output in a textfile.

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => (r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int], r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int], r.getField(2).asInstanceOf[Int], r.getField(3).asInstanceOf[Double], r.getField(4).asInstanceOf[Double], r.getField(5).asInstanceOf[Double])

operations.thatKeyUdf: (li: (Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double)) => li._2

operations.udf: (t: (Int, (Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double))) => t._2

operations.thisKeyUdf: (li: (Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double)) => s"${li._2}|${li._3}"
(t: ((Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double), (Int, Int, Double))) => t._1._3
(t: (((Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double), (Int, Int, Double)), (Int, Int))) => t._2._2

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val ord = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val d = r.getField(1).toString; val year = if (d != null && d.length >= 4) d.substring(0,4).toInt else 0; (ord, year) }

operations.thisKeyUdf: (t: ((((Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double), (Int, Int, Double)), (Int, Int)), (Int, String))) => t._1._1._1._1

operations.udf: (t: (((( (Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double), (Int, Int, Double)), (Int, Int)), (Int, String)), (Int, Int))) => { val li = t._1._1._1._1; val ps = t._1._1._1._2; val n  = t._1._2; val o  = t._2; val nation = n._2; val year = o._2; val l_extendedprice = li._4; val l_discount = li._5; val l_quantity = li._6; val ps_supplycost = ps._3; val profit = l_extendedprice * (1.0 - l_discount) - (ps_supplycost * l_quantity); ((nation, year), profit) }
(a: ((String, Int), Double), b: ((String, Int), Double)) => (a._1, a._2 + b._2)

log.thoughts: Join part→lineitem→partsupp→supplier→nation→orders. Filter parts by name containing 'green', extract order year, compute profit per line, then aggregate by nation and year, and write to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT s_suppkey, s_nationkey FROM supplier) as X

data.thisKeyUdf: (t: ((Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double), (Int, Int, Double))) => t._1._3

data.table: (SELECT n_nationkey, n_name FROM nation) as X

data.thisKeyUdf: (t: (((Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double), (Int, Int, Double)), (Int, Int))) => t._2._2

data.table: (SELECT o_orderkey, o_orderdate FROM orders) as X

data.thisKeyUdf: (t: ((((Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double), (Int, Int, Double)), (Int, Int)), (Int, String))) => t._1._1._1._1

data.udf: (t: (((( (Int, Int, Int, Double, Double, Double), (Int, Int, Double)), (Int, Int)), (Int, String)), (Int, Int))) => { val li = t._1._1._1._1; val ps = t._1._1._1._2; val n  = t._1._2; val o  = t._2; val nation = n._2; val year = o._2; val l_extendedprice = li._4; val l_discount = li._5; val l_quantity = li._6; val ps_supplycost = ps._3; val profit = l_extendedprice * (1.0 - l_discount) - (ps_supplycost * l_quantity); ((nation, year), profit) }
